1.2 计算 Q 值¶

Q-Learning Q-Learning Value IterationPolicy Iteration-ValueUtility

Q-Learning Q - Q

$$ q(s_{t},a) = R_{t+1} + \gamma \times\max_a q(a,s_{t+1}) $$

- $(s_{t},a)$ $a$ $R_{t+1}$ $a$ $s_{t+1}$Q $\max_a q(a,s_{t+1})$$\gamma$

Q $alpha$ Q

$$ q(s_{t},a) = (1-\alpha) \times q(s_{t},a) + \alpha \times(R_{t+1} + \gamma \times\max_a q(a,s_{t+1})) $$

2 $q(s_{t},a)$

$s_1$ u $s_2$ Q u: -24r: -13d: -0.29l: +40$\gamma$ 0.9

$$ \begin{align} q(s_{t},a) & = R_{t+1} + \gamma \times\max_a q(a,s_{t+1}) \\ & =(-0.1) + (0.9)*(40) \\ & =(35.9) \end{align} $$

import random

actions = ['u','r','d','l']
qline = {'u':1.2, 'r':-2.1, 'd':-24.5, 'l':27}
epsilon = 0.3 # 0.3

def choose_action(epsilon):
    
    action = None
    if random.uniform(0,1) < 0.3: # 
        # 
        action = random.choice(actions)
    else: 
        #  Q 
        action = max(qline, key=qline.get)
    return action

对几个关键参数的理解：¶

epsilon¶

epsilon-greedy $$ \Large \pi \left (a|s \right ) \leftarrow \begin{cases} 1 - \epsilon + \frac{\epsilon}{|A(s)|} & \text{if } { a=\mathop{argmax}\limits_{{a}'\in A(s)} Q(s,{a}')} \\ \frac{\epsilon}{|A(s)|} & \text{otherwise} \end{cases} $$

, Qtable epsilonepsilonepsilon

alpha 和 gamma¶

Q: $$ \Large Q(S_{t},A_{t})\leftarrow (1 - \alpha)Q(S_{t},A_{t}) + \alpha(R_{t+1} + \gamma\mathop{max}\limits_{{a}\in A}Q(S_{t+1},a)) $$

alphaalphaalphagammagammagamma

def parameter_lab(epsilon0=0.5, alpha=0.5, gamma=0.9, epsfunc=None):
    g = Maze("test_world\maze_01.txt",trap_number=5)
    r = Robot(g,alpha=alpha, epsilon0=epsilon0, gamma=gamma, epsfunc=epsfunc)
    r.set_status(learning=True)

    runner = Runner(r, g)
    runner.run_training(50, display_direction=True)
    runner.plot_results()

第一组：两种衰减方式¶

In [58]:
def epsfunc_sqrt(eps0, t, eps):
    return eps0 / math.sqrt(t)

def epsfunc_linear(eps0, t, eps):
    return eps0 - t * 0.1
In [59]:
